President Barack Obama has announced his intention to nominate Sharon E. Burke as the Director of Operational Energy Plans and Programs at the Department of Defense, and Marilyn A. Brown as a Member of the Board of Directors of the Tennessee Valley Authority. Sharon E. Burke is currently a Vice President at the Center for a New American Security, where she focuses on "Natural Security" and has published studies on energy security and climate change. Marilyn A. Brown is an endowed Professor of Energy Policy at the Georgia Institute of Technology and has worked at the U.S. Department of Energy's Oak Ridge National Laboratory. She is the author of over 200 publications and has received numerous honors and awards for her work in energy efficiency.